The '''Kaiser Crab''' is a {{2|Bosses|Boss}} encounter found in {{2|Hive}}. It consists of two arms that fight simultaneously: the [[Crusher]] (left claw) and the [[Rocket]] (right claw). Players are {{BD|Surrounded||2}} — attacks from behind deal 50% more damage depending on which arm the player is facing away from.

== Crusher ==
{{Enemy Infobox|Crusher|2}}
=== Pattern ===
{{Intents|Crusher|2}}
Crusher cycles through its five moves in a fixed order, repeating forever:
# {{Int|Crusher|Thrash||2}}
# {{Int|Crusher|Enlarging Strike||2}}
# {{Int|Crusher|Bug Sting||2}}
# {{Int|Crusher|Adapt||2}}
# {{Int|Crusher|Guarded Strike||2}}

{{Clear}}

== Rocket ==
{{Enemy Infobox|Rocket|2}}

=== Pattern ===
{{Intents|Rocket|2}}
Rocket cycles through its five moves in a fixed order, repeating forever:
# {{Int|Rocket|Targeting Reticle||2}}
# {{Int|Rocket|Precision Beam||2}}
# {{Int|Rocket|Charge Up||2}}
# {{Int|Rocket|Laser||2}}
# {{Int|Rocket|Recharge||2}}

{{Clear}}

==Interactions==
===Anti-Synergies===
* Effects that automate {{QueryLink|Cards|type:Attack|Attacks|2}} toward random targets (such as {{C|Hellraiser||2}}, {{C|Mayhem||2}}, and {{R|History Course||2}}) can potentially turn the player away from the claw attacking for a given turn, leaving them exposed to additional damage via {{BD|Surrounded||2}}.
**{{C|Stampede||2}} can be particularly dangerous, as its trigger occurs after the player has ended their turn.

